DSBT-SRCH-TXNID: /disburse/search/{transaction_id}/{summary_only}

Get disbursement processing status by polling
1. This end point is avaiable to poll disbursement processing status info.
2. It is recommended to fetch with default summay_only flag to reduce load on the systems.
3. Disbursement processing systems may chose to implement rate limiting at transaction_id level to avoid request flooding.

Authorizations:
x-access-token
path Parameters
transaction_id
required
string <= 99 characters
Example: 12345678901234567000

Unique transaction id set by sender as part of the initiating request to co-relate requests across interface end point, sessions, etc., For e.g transaction_id be used to find status using GET call or correlate the transaction as part of the callback call.

summary_only
required
boolean
Default: true

Optional. Defualt is false, If summary_only set to true then only the message header with stats / status to be returend as part of implementation

header Parameters
accept-language
string
Example: en

Default value: en

timestamp
required
string
Example: Tue, 06 Mar 2020 21:00:00 GMT

request timestamp in HTTP Date format - Tue, 06 Mar 2020 21:00:00 GMT

Responses

Sandbox Server

https://sandbox.dpg.org/v0.1.0/disburse/search/{transaction_id}/{summary_only}

Response samples

  • 401
  • 403
  • 500
  • default
Content type
application/json
{
  • "error": {
    • "code": "string",
    • "message": "string"
    }
}

DSBT-SRCH-REFID : /disburse/search/{reference_id}

Get disbursement processing status by polling using reference_id
1. This end point is avaiable to poll disbursement processing status info.
2. Disbursement processing systems may chose to implement rate limiting at reference_id level to avoid request flooding.

Authorizations:
x-access-token
path Parameters
reference_id
required
string
Example: 12345678901234567890

Unique reference id set by business txn initiating system. Used for co-relating the callback requests and to get status info

header Parameters
accept-language
string
Example: en

Default value: en

timestamp
required
string
Example: Tue, 06 Mar 2020 21:00:00 GMT

request timestamp in HTTP Date format - Tue, 06 Mar 2020 21:00:00 GMT
